Runyan Ranches
September 10 at 5:21 AM ·

If you’re cold, their cold...bring them inside! Lol Zoom got some coffee going and threw on a snuggly robe. Crazy couple of cold days that the animals weren’t totally prepared for, but Adam got the heat going in the barns and so far everyone is doing great. Dress warm if you are coming to play today; it is suppose to be pretty by this weekend! Have a blessed day!

Loving Municipal Schools

shared_text:
Devon Energy
July 21 at 10:36 AM ·

Devon is humbled to receive the Loving Municipal Schools Board's annual Excellence in Student Achievement Award. 🙂

Each year the New Mexico School Boards Association allows districts to nominate leaders who have played an important role in improving student achievement at the local and district level. We strive to be a significant contributor to the education of students wherever we operate, so this recognition is impactful for all of our employees in southeast New Mexico. 🙌

We are proud of the contributions we make to improve STEM education for the teachers and students, and best is yet to come!

We are committed to southeast New Mexico and look forward to finding solutions to improve the community – TOGETHER. Thank you to the Loving Municipal School Board for recognizing our commitment to student achievement and inspiring our next generation of community leaders.

New Mexico Activities Association (NMAA)
May 27 at 12:19 PM ·

NMAA message to students, coaches, administrators and parents:
There have been many posts on social media indicating what will take place in the Fall with regards to schools and athletics/activities. Please assume that all information is false unless it comes directly from Governor Michelle Lujan-Grisham, Lieutenant Governor Howie Morales, Secretary of Education Ryan Stewart, or the New Mexico Activities Association. Currently, there is a task force that is making the decisions on the state’s efforts to return to school.
#WeWillPlayAgainNM

Lee White, Superintendent

SkillsUSA NM
April 9 at 11:13 AM ·

The highlighted member for this week is Bianca Solano. Bianca is a senior attending Loving High School. She has been a member of SkillsUSA for one year now, but she has definitely made it count. She has participated in various SkillsUSA events, such as volunteering in Ruidoso, and participating in round house. Her favorite part of being in skills is trying different things, and getting involved in the community. Being in SkillsUSA has taught Bianca how to be a better leader. She says “the experiences I have gained from SkillsUSA are invaluable.” Thank you, Bianca, for being an asset to your SkillsUSA chapter and community! To be recognized as a highlighted member or to nominate someone to be a highlighted member reach out to your SkillsUSA NM state officers!

New Mexico Public Education Department
April 2 at 9:37 AM ·

Beginning on Monday, New Mexico public broadcasting channels will air instructional content to support families and K-5 students learning at home. Albuquerque Public Schools has taken the lead in producing the lessons, but you do not need to be an APS student to benefit. The broadcast schedule is posted below, but lessons will also be posted on the APS YouTube channel so that you can watch the lessons at the time that works best for your family. Videos will be ASL accessible and available in English and Spanish. This is just one inspiring way that New Mexicans across the state are collaborating to make quality instruction accessible to all students. Thank you, New Mexico PBS for being an incredible partner in this ambitious project!
